# ============================================
# CLIENT PRODUCTION ENV (Vercel)
# ============================================
# These go in: Vercel Dashboard → Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# Environment = "Production" for the live URL.
# You can also set them per-preview for staging branches.
# ============================================

# Backend API URL.
# On a single-Vercel-project setup (this project), the client and the
# Express server share the same origin, so a RELATIVE path works —
# no need to set this at all in production. The client falls back to
# "/api" (see client/src/lib/api.ts).
#
# If you ever split the API to a different host (Render, Railway, etc.),
# you would set it to the full URL like:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://your-api-host.example.com/api
#
# Leave blank in production on a single Vercel project.
VITE_API_URL=

# Stripe publishable key (the LIVE key, NOT test, in production)
# Get at: https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_LIVE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
